TopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525766\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ama1665702895903.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ama1665702895903.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ama1665702895903.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ama1665702895903\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Define Stored Procedure Components\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">After creating a store procedure, you need to define its signature in Uniface.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ama1665702895903__li_d18530e1_d18531e1_d18532e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ama1665702895903__p_d36320e1_d36321e1_d36322e1\">Develop and thoroughly test the DBMS stored\n               procedure. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">For information on DBMS-specific implementation and operation requirements, see\n               the relevant DBMS driver information.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ama1665702895903__li_d18533e1_d18534e1_d18535e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">In the Signature Editor, created a new modeled component. Select <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Stored Procedure Component</span> as the implementation type.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ama1665702895903__li_d18536e1_d18537e1_d18538e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Define the operations (and their parameters) associated with the stored procedure. Optionally, enter comments for internal documentation purposes in the appropriate <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Comment</span> fields.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ama1665702895903__li_d18539e1_d18540e1_d18541e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Ensure that the stored procedure component is defined as stateless. This is necessary because a stored procedure is called as a global operation, and not as a single instance.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ama1665702895903__li_d18542e1_d18543e1_d18544e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File &gt;Compile Signature</span></span>.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqa1665702772542.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures</a><p>For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ffw1719409087502.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SQL and Stored Procedures Support</a><p>For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pau1665702776582.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures</a><p>Create a signature for a service stored procedure, in which one or more stored procedures are represented to Uniface as operations.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525766\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525766\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Stored Procedure Components Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Stored Procedure Components After creating a store procedure, you need to define its signature in Uniface. Develop and thoroughly test the DBMS stored procedure. For information on DBMS-specific implementation and operation requirements, see the relevant DBMS driver information. In the Signature Editor, created a new modeled component. Select Stored Procedure Component as the implementation type. Define the operations (and their parameters) associated with the stored procedure. Optionally, enter comments for internal documentation purposes in the appropriate Comment fields. Ensure that the stored procedure component is defined as stateless. This is necessary because a stored procedure is called as a global operation, and not as a single instance. Select File >Compile Signature . Related Links Naming Specifications for Service Store Procedures For Service Stored Procedures, the signature of the Stored Procedure Component maps the names of Uniface components, operations, and parameters to the name of a package, procedure, and parameter names in the procedure. SQL and Stored Procedures Support For SQL-enabled databases, you can use the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor to send SQL instructions to the database. Some databases also support stored procedures. Define Signatures for Service Stored Procedures Create a signature for a service stored procedure, in which one or more stored procedures are represented to Uniface as operations. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}